	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I created a custom CSS to allow the content of a specific page to look almost like the original nesdev front page.
<br />
<br />Here's the current wip <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NesdevTest" class="postlink">here</a>.
<br />
<br />The way it works is either you insert CSS style in the page or include a CSS that exist on the server on it. That CSS must overwrite the existing style to allow to remove parts and set the things the way you want.
<br />
<br />How is it so far Memblers? Is it getting close to the original page? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />Edit:
<br />
<br />When logged in to the wiki, with the right query string parameters, you can edit that page. I'm still thinking of a more elegant way to do it thought.

		

